HEADWORD: Inverness cape
<hw>In`ver*ness" cape"</hw></mhw>. <def>A kind of full sleeveless cape,
fitting closely about the neck.</def></p>

<p><q>Robert's wind-blown head and tall form wrapped in an
<qex>Inverness cape</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs. Humphry
Ward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inverse</ent>⟦br⟧
